.TH simple_shell 1 "17 August 2023" "0.1" "simple_shell man page"

.SH NAME
simple_shell - Simple shell written in C for interacting with a Linux operating system.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell is a command-line program that reads lines from either a file or the terminal, interprets them, and executes other commands. It serves as the interface for users to interact with the operating system. The shell understands and executes commands a user enters, providing a command syntax for interacting with the system.

.PP
.B Overview
The simple shell is the program that is started when a user logs into the system. It offers features to aid interactive use and supports both interactive and non-interactive use (shell scripts). Users can input commands directly to the running shell or place them in a file for direct execution.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns 0 on success and a non-zero value on failure.

.SH PATH
The simple_shell looks for executables in all directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

.SH OPTIONS
Command options are typed after the main command, followed by a space and a '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLES
To list the contents of a directory:
.BR $ ls -l

.SH BUGS
A single space is required after each argument.

.SH AUTHOR
The simple_shell man page was written by Mthobezi Sikhosana

